stylometry: A higher wait time means having less employees at lower wages and lower customer service, however supplying products at lower prices. A low wait time in lines means having more employees at higher wages and high customer satisfaction, but also higher priced products to the consumers. The cost of more employees is higher costs to the company, and higher priced products, which means maybe a loss of a customer base to lower-priced competitors, however giving a superior level of customer service. The cost of low amount of employees is the low amount of customer satisfaction, yet it allows you to deliver low prices to the consumer. The objective is to find the right amount of employees to cashier which will deliver enough customer service satisfaction, but still allow for prices to be low.
